  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6814.64 sitting right between the massive negative gamma walls at 6810 (-62.2B) and 6815 (-48.3B), dealers are in active buy mode as they hedge short gamma positions into this selloff. The breakout regime combined with the wall break and GEX surge events suggests dealers will continue amplifying moves - buying any dips toward 6810 and selling rallies toward the positive gamma cap at 6830. Watch for violent whipsaws in this 6810-6830 range as dealers flip between buying and selling based on directional moves.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect wild swings between 6810 and 6830 with dealers pushing price action in whatever direction it starts moving.",
